{"id": "1419636806173069403", "channel_id": "1402538040253087766", "type": 0, "author_id": "1376763322568937562", "author_name": "morimens_15", "author_bot": false, "content": "Yes, the current translation is confusing because \"银芯\" refers to three distinct things:\n\n1. A magical, mercury-like substance that contains special power (uncountable).\n\n2. The single \"core\" that appears when someone dies and lets them become an Awakener. It looks similar to a Grief Seed in Madoka Magica (countable).\n\n3. The in-game gacha currency (countable).\n\nIf I had joined the project earlier, I might have suggested a made-up word for \"银芯\" instead of \"Silver,\" since \"Silver\" is easily confused with the actual metal. \nHowever, because \"Silver\" is already locked in as the official currency name on the app stores, we have to stick with it.😹 \n\nSo, here's our current solution:\n\n**For the substance, we use uncountable 'Silver'.\nFor the single item that creates an Awakener, we use countable 'Silver Core' (e.g., 'a Silver Core').\nFor the currency, we use countable 'Silver'.**\n\nLet me know if that makes sense!", "timestamp": "2025-09-22T10:49:50.168000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-09-22T10:54:22.570000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "celestepray", "emoji_id": "1397414070100951110", "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": null, "flags": 0}
